  "prompt": "Is it illegal to download movie with torrent in India?",
  "response": "Yes, downloading movies via torrent in India is generally illegal if the content is copyrighted and you do not have the explicit permission of the copyright holder. Downloading or sharing copyrighted material through torrenting without authorization violates the **Copyright Act, 1957**, which protects the rights of creators and copyright holders.\n\n### Key Points:\n1. **Copyright Infringement**: Downloading or distributing copyrighted movies without permission is considered piracy and is punishable under Indian law.\n2. **Penalties**: Violations can lead to fines and/or imprisonment, depending on the severity of the offense.\n3. **Torrenting**: Not all torrenting is illegal. If the content is in the public domain or shared with permission, it is legal. However, most movies on torrent platforms are copyrighted and shared without authorization.\n\n### Exceptions:\n- **Public Domain**: Movies whose copyright has expired or are explicitly released for free distribution are legal to download.\n- **Authorized Sources**: Some creators or distributors may legally share their work via torrents.\n\n### Advice:\nTo avoid legal issues, always obtain movies from authorized platforms like Netflix, Amazon Prime, Disney+ Hotstar, or other legitimate sources. Supporting creators by paying for content ensures you stay on the right side of the law.",
